reviews.review: I've seen every one of these in the theaters from 1977, bought all the toys as a kid, and marched in the 501st Legion.  This restored my faith in Star Wars after the last film. My group all game out happy and I'm pleased JJ Abrams was able to get it done right.

Battling back from Last Jedi that took the trilogy arc off the rails, Rise of Skywalker does the best it can closing out the Saga and piecing everything back together. The cinematography is outstanding and it’s unlike any Star Wars movie that’s come before it. A very worthy and satisfying end to the saga.

It was the best Star Wars movie I've ever seen. I read some of the critic's reviews, and they were wrong. This is a true masterpiece fans would expect. I know it won't satisfy all Star Wars fans, but this is packed with thrills, humor, action, and heart. The ending is also great too! It's worth the ticket and a must see for all fans. Just ignore the critics and review for yourself.

Don't fret if the first 20 minutes feel a little disjointed. It feels like that time is used to reset from Last Jedi. Once the movie gets underway, everything comes together. There's some tremendously good action sequences, and the musical score is incredible. Nothing really feels out of place. The term "nice save" comes to mind. It really is an enjoyable movie.
Just saw this for the second time, liked it even more. Man, I love this movie!
A must see critics are wrong

Much better than TLJ. Better than I was originally anticipating. Certainly the best of the new trilogy. The bar was admittedly low and it definitely has its share of flaws. It never quite reaches the greatness of the original films. However, there are some very memorable moments awaiting long time fans.
Great start to finish. Some jokes definitely aimed toward children, and persistent sarcasm for adults. A must see!
JJ  just dunked on Rian. AMAZING!! this is what a STARWARS movie is supposed to be.  excellent end to film's most loved saga.
Absolutely loved this movie! Very satisfying ending to the Skywalker saga! Defiantly going to go and see this film several times.
